<% af_category "Digital vs. Traditional Menu Boards" do %>
  <h2>Digital Menu Boards</h2>
  <p>
    Digital menu boards a increasing in popularity and, in the long run, are more cost effective. These boards are much easier to edit if you
    happen to introduce a new item - so there is no need to have a new menu board made - and can be day-parted to change over from one menu to another. 
    For example, if your business sells breakfast then your digital menu board can be automated to change from a breakfast menu to a lunch 
    menu at a certain time and can even be updated in real-time. These boards can also be used to cycle through images so you can have numerous 
    boards set up to show both the menu as well as select items. Additionally, graphic artists can be hired to design these menu boards and 
    style them to your liking.
  </p>

  <h2>Traditional Menu Boards</h2>
  <p>
    While digital menu boards are becoming more commonplace, traditional menu boards are still effective. The obvious benefit of using a 
    traditional menu board is that there is no risk of digital or electrical errors. While digital menu boards have many benefits there is
    also the potential cost of maintaining those boards that you should consider. Traditional menu boards require little to no maintenance 
    and are simple to install, as they do not require the electrical wiring needed for digital menu boards.
  </p>
<% end %>

<% af_category "Take-out and Online Menus" do %>
  <p>
    Regardless of whether you decide to have a digital or traditional menu board, you should also have some paper menus availble for patrons 
    to take home or examine more carefully. You should also provide an online menu on all of your social media outlets and website. Many 
    customer prefer to see what an establishment has to offer before visiting so they can cut down on their wait time. Prevents indecisive
    customers from holding up the line and can keep your operations running smoothly.
  </p>
<% end %>

